Package: guttmanimpute
Title: Targeted Imputation of Misfit Ordinal Responses in a Guttman Scale
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Sherwin E.", "Balbuena", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "balbuenasherwine@debesmscat.edu.ph")
Description: Implements the targeted imputation method described in Balbuena
    (2024) for replacing misfitting ordinal responses at the intersection of
    misfit persons and misfit items within a Guttman scale. The package
    rearranges response data into Guttman order (descending row totals then
    descending column totals), fits a Partial Credit Model via the 'eRm'
    package to identify misfit persons and items using Outfit/Infit mean-square
    fit statistics, replaces each misfit-intersection cell with the nearest
    integer to the average of its surrounding neighbours (k = 1), and
    restores the data to its original row/column order. Both the
    Guttman-ordered dataset and the final imputed dataset can be saved to
    CSV files.
